Note:
COMPILE ORCHESTRATOR - Per-File Compile Pipeline (Layer 3 of P1-E v3)

This file authors the program-level compile orchestrator that the
v0.0.8.5 driver layer assumes exists. It consumes the imports-merged
AST root and emits a target assembly file via the full
AST -> HIR -> MIR -> optimize_program -> LIR -> machine_code pipeline.

Authored in the same commit as the WPA work (Layer 1) and the
optimize_program glue (Layer 2) per CEO directive against orphan-code
shipment: compile_program is what wires the entire P1-E pipeline into
real builds.

Three callers existed prior to this file at:
- compiler/driver/compiler_driver.runa:220
- compiler/driver/build_system.runa:570
- compiler/driver/parallel_compilation.runa:524
all of which invoke compile_program(program, output_path) and expect the
0=success / nonzero=failure return convention. This file satisfies that
contract.

Public surface:
- compile_program(program, output_path) -> Integer
- set_active_build_context(ctx) -> Integer
- get_active_opt_level() -> Integer
- dispatch_codegen_by_arch(arch, lir_module, config) -> Integer
- get_target_os_from_config() -> Integer
- get_target_arch_from_config() -> Integer
- map_tm_os_to_machine_code_os(tm_os) -> Integer
- map_tm_arch_to_machine_code_arch(tm_arch) -> Integer
:End Note

